Conditions at the Rahima Moosa Mother and Child Hospital in Johannesburg remain in the news. The hospital suspended a doctor after he exposed the appalling conditions. Dr. Tim de Maayer has been re-instated after the Gauteng health MEC intervened. For more, eNCA speaks to Dr Cedric Sihlangu from the South African Medical Association Trade Union. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Dr. Cedric Sihlangu from the South African Medical Association Trade Union says the state of public hospitals in South Africa is a national problem. He says the conditions in hospitals and the treatment of staff must be dealt with at the national government level. WATCH | Rahima Moosa doctor reinstated Conditions at the Rahima Moosa Mother and Child Hospital in Johannesburg have again highlighted the call for this. A doctor at the hospital was suspended after he exposed the appalling conditions. Dr. Tim de Maayer has been re-instated after the Gauteng health MEC intervened.